a3ComFddiSMTTable.name: a3ComFddiSMTTable
a3ComFddiSMTTable.description: A list of optional SMT entries. The number of entries shall not exceed the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber.

a3ComFddiSMTEntry.name: a3ComFddiSMTEntry
a3ComFddiSMTEntry.description: An optional SMT entry containing information common to a given optional SMT.

a3ComFddiSMTIndex.name: a3ComFddiSMTIndex
a3ComFddiSMTIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber. The value for each SMT must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

a3ComFddiSMTManufacturerOUI.name: a3ComFddiSMTManufacturerOUI
a3ComFddiSMTManufacturerOUI.description: The three octets of manufacturer data which make up the manufacturerOUI component.

a3ComFddiSMTManufacturerData.name: a3ComFddiSMTManufacturerData
a3ComFddiSMTManufacturerData.description: The 29 octets of manufacturer data which make up the manufacturerData component.

a3ComFddiSMTHoldState.name: a3ComFddiSMTHoldState
a3ComFddiSMTHoldState.description: This variable indicates the current state of the Hold function. The value 'not-holding' is the default and initial value. The value must be set to 'not-holding' as part of Active-Actions and when the conditions causing 'holding-prm' or 'holding-sec' are no longer true. The value 'holding-prm' must be set when the condition (notTR-Flag & not RE-Flag & (PC-LS=QLS | LEM-Fail TNE>NS-Max | (not LS-Flag & TPC > T-Out))) is satisfied in state PC8:ACTIVE for the A Port. The value 'holding-sec' must be set when the condition (notTR-Flag & not RE-Flag & (PC-LS=QLS | LEM-Fail TNE>NS-Max | (not LS-Flag & TPC > T-Out))) is satisfied in state PC8:ACTIVE for the B Port.

a3ComFddiSMTSetCount.name: a3ComFddiSMTSetCount
a3ComFddiSMTSetCount.description: This variable is composed of a count incremented in response to a Set operation on the MIB, and the time of the change, however only the count is reported here (refer to ANSI SMT 8.4.1).

a3ComFddiSMTLastSetStationId.name: a3ComFddiSMTLastSetStationId
a3ComFddiSMTLastSetStationId.description: The Station ID of the station that effected the last change in the FDDI MIB.

a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionTable.name: a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionTable
a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionTable.description: A list of MAC bridge function entries.

a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionEntry.name: a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionEntry
a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionEntry.description: Bridge function information for a given MAC within a given SMT.

a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionSMTIndex.name: a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionSMTIndex
a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionSMTIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber. The value for each SMT must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionMACIndex.name: a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionMACIndex
a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctionMACIndex.description: Index variable for uniquely identifying the MAC object instances.

a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctions.name: a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctions
a3ComFddiMACBridgeFunctions.description: Indicates the MAC's optional bridging functions. The Value -1 is used to indicate that bridging is not supported by this MAC. The value is a sum. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each function present, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. The powers are according to the following table: Function Power tb 0 -- Transparent bridging active sr 1 -- Src routing active srt 2 -- Src routing transparent active

a3ComFddiMACTPriTable.name: a3ComFddiMACTPriTable
a3ComFddiMACTPriTable.description: A list of MAC T-Pri entries.

a3ComFddiMACTPriEntry.name: a3ComFddiMACTPriEntry
a3ComFddiMACTPriEntry.description: A collection of T-Pri information for a given MAC within a given SMT.

a3ComFddiMACTPriSMTIndex.name: a3ComFddiMACTPriSMTIndex
a3ComFddiMACTPriSMTIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber. The value for each SMT must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

a3ComFddiMACTPriMACIndex.name: a3ComFddiMACTPriMACIndex
a3ComFddiMACTPriMACIndex.description: Index variable for uniquely identifying the MAC object instances.

a3ComFddiMACTPri0.name: a3ComFddiMACTPri0
a3ComFddiMACTPri0.description: This attribute is an unsigned twos-complement T-pri threshold as described in the MAC standard converted to non-twos-complement form and reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiMACTPri1.name: a3ComFddiMACTPri1
a3ComFddiMACTPri1.description: This attribute is an unsigned twos-complement T-pri threshold as described in the MAC standard converted to non-twos-complement form and reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiMACTPri2.name: a3ComFddiMACTPri2
a3ComFddiMACTPri2.description: This attribute is an unsigned twos-complement T-pri threshold as described in the MAC standard converted to non-twos-complement form and reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiMACTPri3.name: a3ComFddiMACTPri3
a3ComFddiMACTPri3.description: This attribute is an unsigned twos-complement T-pri threshold as described in the MAC standard converted to non-twos-complement form and reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiMACTPri4.name: a3ComFddiMACTPri4
a3ComFddiMACTPri4.description: This attribute is an unsigned twos-complement T-pri threshold as described in the MAC standard converted to non-twos-complement form and reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiMACTPri5.name: a3ComFddiMACTPri5
a3ComFddiMACTPri5.description: This attribute is an unsigned twos-complement T-pri threshold as described in the MAC standard converted to non-twos-complement form and reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiMACTPri6.name: a3ComFddiMACTPri6
a3ComFddiMACTPri6.description: This attribute is an unsigned twos-complement T-pri threshold as described in the MAC standard converted to non-twos-complement form and reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiPATHRingTable.name: a3ComFddiPATHRingTable
a3ComFddiPATHRingTable.description: A list of PATH ring entries.

a3ComFddiPATHRingEntry.name: a3ComFddiPATHRingEntry
a3ComFddiPATHRingEntry.description: Ring latency, trace status, and T-Rmode information for a given PATH within a given SMT.

a3ComFddiPATHRingSMTIndex.name: a3ComFddiPATHRingSMTIndex
a3ComFddiPATHRingSMTIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber. The value for each SMT must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

a3ComFddiPATHRingPATHIndex.name: a3ComFddiPATHRingPATHIndex
a3ComFddiPATHRingPATHIndex.description: Index variable for uniquely identifying the primary, secondary and local PATH object instances. Local PATH object instances are represented with integer values 3 to 255.

a3ComFddiPATHRingLatency.name: a3ComFddiPATHRingLatency
a3ComFddiPATHRingLatency.description: Gives the total accumulated latency of the ring associated with this path. May be measured directly by the station or calculated by a management station. Values of this object are reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiPATHTraceStatus.name: a3ComFddiPATHTraceStatus
a3ComFddiPATHTraceStatus.description: This attribute indicates the current trace status of the path. The value is a sum which represents all of the trace status information which applies. This value initially takes the value zero, then for each condition which applies, 2 raised to a power is added to the sum. the powers are according to the following table: TraceStatus Power traceinitiated 0 tracepropragated 1 traceterminated 2 tracetimeout 3

a3ComFddiPATHT_Rmode.name: a3ComFddiPATHT_Rmode
a3ComFddiPATHT_Rmode.description: Used by RMT to limit the duration of restricted dialogs on a path. This object is reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiPATHSbaTable.name: a3ComFddiPATHSbaTable
a3ComFddiPATHSbaTable.description: A list of PATH Sba entries.

a3ComFddiPATHSbaEntry.name: a3ComFddiPATHSbaEntry
a3ComFddiPATHSbaEntry.description: Sba information for a given PATH within a given SMT.

a3ComFddiPATHSbaSMTIndex.name: a3ComFddiPATHSbaSMTIndex
a3ComFddiPATHSbaSMTIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber. The value for each SMT must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

a3ComFddiPATHSbaPATHIndex.name: a3ComFddiPATHSbaPATHIndex
a3ComFddiPATHSbaPATHIndex.description: Index variable for uniquely identifying the primary, secondary and local PATH object instances. Local PATH object instances are represented with integer values 3 to 255.

a3ComFddiPATHSbaPayload.name: a3ComFddiPATHSbaPayload
a3ComFddiPATHSbaPayload.description: The payload portion of the Synchronous Bandwidth Allocation for thi path. This value represents the maximum number of bytes of data allocated for transmission per 125 microseconds.

a3ComFddiPATHSbaOverhead.name: a3ComFddiPATHSbaOverhead
a3ComFddiPATHSbaOverhead.description: The overhead portion of the Synchronous Bandwith Allocation for this path. This value repersents the maximum number of bytes overhead (token capture, frame header, etc.) used pre negotiated Target Token Rotation Time (T-neg).

a3ComFddiPATHSbaAvailable.name: a3ComFddiPATHSbaAvailable
a3ComFddiPATHSbaAvailable.description: This value is the maximum Synchronous Bandwith available for a path in bytes per second.

a3ComFddiPORTTable.name: a3ComFddiPORTTable
a3ComFddiPORTTable.description: A list of optional PORT entries.

a3ComFddiPORTEntry.name: a3ComFddiPORTEntry
a3ComFddiPORTEntry.description: MAC loop time and EB error count information for a given PORT within a given SMT.

a3ComFddiPORTSMTIndex.name: a3ComFddiPORTSMTIndex
a3ComFddiPORTSMTIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber. The value for each SMT must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

a3ComFddiPORTIndex.name: a3ComFddiPORTIndex
a3ComFddiPORTIndex.description: Index variable for uniquely identifying the PORT object instances.

a3ComFddiPORTMACLoopTime.name: a3ComFddiPORTMACLoopTime
a3ComFddiPORTMACLoopTime.description: This attribute controls the value used for T-Next(9) (see 9.4.4.2.3). This object is reported in 1 ns units.

a3ComFddiPORTEBErrorCt.name: a3ComFddiPORTEBErrorCt
a3ComFddiPORTEBErrorCt.description: A count that should as closely as possible match the times an Elasticity Buffer Error has occurred while in active line state.

a3ComFddiPORTLSTable.name: a3ComFddiPORTLSTable
a3ComFddiPORTLSTable.description: A list of optional PORT line state entries.

a3ComFddiPORTLSEntry.name: a3ComFddiPORTLSEntry
a3ComFddiPORTLSEntry.description: Maintenance line state and PC line state information for a given PORT within a given SMT.

a3ComFddiPORTLSSMTIndex.name: a3ComFddiPORTLSSMTIndex
a3ComFddiPORTLSSMTIndex.description: A unique value for each SMT. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of snmpFddiSMTNumber. The value for each SMT must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

a3ComFddiPORTLSPORTIndex.name: a3ComFddiPORTLSPORTIndex
a3ComFddiPORTLSPORTIndex.description: Index variable for uniquely identifying the PORT object instances.

a3ComFddiPORTMaintLS.name: a3ComFddiPORTMaintLS
a3ComFddiPORTMaintLS.description: The PORT Maintenance Line State specifies the line state (Maint-LS) to be transmitted when the PCM state machine for the port is in state PC9 Maint.

a3ComFddiPORTPCLS.name: a3ComFddiPORTPCLS
a3ComFddiPORTPCLS.description: This attribute indicates the line state (PC-LS) received by the port.

a3ComFddiSMTHoldCondition.name: a3ComFddiSMTHoldCondition
a3ComFddiSMTHoldCondition.description: Generated when fddiSMTHoldState (fddimibSMTHoldState) assumes the state holding-prm or holding-sec. This notification is a Condition in the Status Report Protocol (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiSMTPeerWrapCondition.name: a3ComFddiSMTPeerWrapCondition
a3ComFddiSMTPeerWrapCondition.description: This condition is active when fddiSMTPeerWrapFlag (fddimibSMTPeerWrapFlag) is set. This notification is a Condition in the Status Report Protocol (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiMACDuplicateAddressCondition.name: a3ComFddiMACDuplicateAddressCondition
a3ComFddiMACDuplicateAddressCondition.description: This condition is active when either fddiMACDA-Flag (fddimibMACDaFlag) or fddiMACUNDA-Flag (fddimibMACUnaDaFlag) is set. This event is handled as a Condition in the Status Report Protocol (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiMACFrameErrorCondition.name: a3ComFddiMACFrameErrorCondition
a3ComFddiMACFrameErrorCondition.description: Generated when the fddiMACFrameErrorRatio (fddimibMACFrameErrorRatio) is greater than or equal to fddiMACFrameErrorThreshold (fddimibMACFrameErrorThreshold). This event is handled as a Condition in the Status Report Protocol (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiMACNotCopiedCondition.name: a3ComFddiMACNotCopiedCondition
a3ComFddiMACNotCopiedCondition.description: Generated when the fddiMACNotCopiedRatio (fddimibMACNotCopiedRatio) is greater than or equal to the fddiMACNotCopiedThreshold (a3ComFddiMACNotCopiedThreshold). This event is handled as a Condition in the Status Report Protocol (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiMACNeighborChangeEvent.name: a3ComFddiMACNeighborChangeEvent
a3ComFddiMACNeighborChangeEvent.description: Generated when a change in a MAC's upstream neighbor address or downstream neighbor address is detected. (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiMACPathChangeEvent.name: a3ComFddiMACPathChangeEvent
a3ComFddiMACPathChangeEvent.description: This event is generated when the value of the fddiMACCurrentPath (fddimibMACCurrentPath) changes. This event shall be supressed if the value changes from isolated to local or local to isolated (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiPORTLerCondition.name: a3ComFddiPORTLerCondition
a3ComFddiPORTLerCondition.description: This condition becomes active when the value of fddiPORTLer-Estimate (fddimibPORTLerEstimate) is less than or equal to fddiPORTLer-Alarm (fddimibPORTLerAlarm). This will be reported with the Status Report Frames (SRF) (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiPORTUndesiredConnAttemptEvent.name: a3ComFddiPORTUndesiredConnAttemptEvent
a3ComFddiPORTUndesiredConnAttemptEvent.description: Generated when an undesired connection attempt has been made (see 5.2.4, 7.2.7, and 8.3).

a3ComFddiPORTEBErrorCondition.name: a3ComFddiPORTEBErrorCondition
a3ComFddiPORTEBErrorCondition.description: Generated when the Elasticity Buffer Error-Ct (a3ComFddiPORTEBErrorCt) increments. This is handled as a condition in the Status Report Protocol. It is generated when an increment occurs in the station's sampling period (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).

a3ComFddiPORTPathChangeEvent.name: a3ComFddiPORTPathChangeEvent
a3ComFddiPORTPathChangeEvent.description: This event is generated when the value of the fddiPORTCurrentPath (a3ComFddiPORTCurrentPath) changes. This event shall be surpressed if the value changes from isolated to local or local to isolated (see 7.2.7 and 8.3).
